# LapViewer Git Workflow (local only)

This repo is **local-only for now**: there is no configured `origin` remote.

## Do not push

- Do **not** run `git push` or try to add/configure a remote unless the user explicitly asks.
- If push fails with "no remote", treat that as expected — report success for local commit/merge instead of retrying push.

## Merge to `dev` when work is done

- Base branch: **`dev`** ([D-004](docs/DECISIONS.md)).
- Feature work lives on `feature/*`, `fix/*`, or `chore/*` branches branched from `dev`.
- After changes are verified (`npm run check`, relevant tests), **merge the feature branch into `dev` locally**:

```bash
git checkout dev
git merge feature/<name>
```

- Prefer a normal merge (no force-push to `dev`).
- Leave the feature branch in place unless the user asks to delete it.

## Commit expectations

- Commit on the feature branch during work; merge to `dev` when the item is complete and verified.
- Never change `git config`, force-push protected branches, or commit secrets ([D-012](docs/DECISIONS.md)).
